text.tspan: Real commodity price index, food products, 1850 to 2015
Real commodity price index, measured relative to prices in the year 1900 (1900 = 100).
Data source: Jacks, D.S. (2019), "From Boom to Bust: A Typology of Real Commodity Prices in the Long Run." Cliometrica 13(2), 202-220.
